<DOC><DOCNO> AP881025-0259 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-25-88 2032EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d f BC-Northwest-Flights     10-25 0110</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Northwest-Flights,0115</SECOND><HEAD>Northwest Airlines to Add Three Asian Flights</HEAD><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Northwest Airlines announced that it will add threenonstop Asian flights next year.   Northwest said Tuesday that it will fly Boeing 747 jetlinerstwice weekly between Tokyo and Saipan, in the Mariana Islands nearGuam, beginning April 1.   The airline also will operate the jumbo jets three times weeklybetween Tokyo and Minneapolis, and three times a week between Osaka,in western Japan, and Los Angeles, both beginning June 3.   Northwest, the fourth-largest U.S. airline, now operates nonstopdaily service from Tokyo to seven U.S. cities: Seattle, SanFrancisco, Los Angeles, Chicago, Detroit, New York and Honolulu.</TEXT></DOC>